## Vim Tips

### Navigation Mode

**page-up&page-down**</br>
`ctrl-f` scrolls down a page and `ctrl-b` scrolls up a page (think "F"orward and "B"ack). </br>
`Ctrl-d` scrolls down half a page, and `ctrl-u` scrolls up half a page.

**navigate block of code** </br>
`{` and `}`

**replace single:** </br>
`:s/some-word/new-word`

**replace globes:** </br>
`%s/some-word/new-word`

**find occures** </br>
`:%s/some-word//gn`

---

### File Exploer Mode (netrw)

**navigate files:** </br>
`:e f<tab>b<tab>b<tab><enter>`

**create a file** </br>
simply hit the `%`. Vim will ask you for a file name.

**create a directory** </br>
simply hit `d`. Vim will ask you for a directory name.

**run files** </br>
`:!python ${your_file_name}.py`


---

### Vim Windows

`ctrl` + `w` + `v`: vertical splitting.</br>
`ctrl` + `w` + `s`: horizontally splitting.</br>
`ctrl` + `w` + `q`: to close one </br>
`ctrl` + `w`, `ctrl` + `w`: switch between windows </br>
[refs](https://superuser.com/questions/486532/how-to-open-files-in-vertically-horizontal-split-windows-in-vim-from-the-command)

